Description: Frame containing 10 fragments of papyrus with hieratic text in black and red ink, and a vignette (depicting the upper part of a female body) in black outlines.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store. Note that no box with a yellow label '24' was located when the material had inventory numbers assigned in 2000; the box labelled '23' is registered as 10700.19.
The frame was labelled as follows by Stephen Quirke: 'unregistered Pap. fragments from Student's Room (15/1/92): two similar to 10988 (and a third? with text only on one side); seven miscellaneous'.
